Úlairë Enquëa, Lieutenant of Morgul    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Okay first off this deck has some obvious flaws - No Armor or Mithril Coat. I didn&#39;t see the wisdom in playing either of those before the DPC but now I do, and Elendil&#39;s Valor is out for Armor, and one Last Alliance is out for Mithril Coat. Not having to take 2 wounds from Uruk-Hai or the Balrog or his little buddy the Cave Troll is goddam more useful than the other junk.<br>
<br><br>
Also it might need one more condition canceller, either another Sleep or Secret Sentinels, probly the latter.<br>
<br><br>
After the warm-up tourney on Friday I was a little panicked at my deck&#39;s inability to deal with Moria swarm, so I went from 2 Gandalf, the Grey Pilgrim to the 4 Friend of Shortpeople and added the Sleep as well. I also switched the Aragorns from Kings in Exile to Rangers of the North. It worked. I didn&#39;t lose to Moria swarm in any of my 10 games that day. My losses were to Uruk-Hai (game 1), beaten to site 9 (game 5), Gabe Alonso&#39;s Uruk-Hai (game 9) and Andy McClure&#39;s Nazgul/strong fellowship that I couldn&#39;t put a dent in (he raced to site 9 also, this was game 10 of the day, but that&#39;s okay cuz his deck was not even remotely straight. go ahead, ask him!).<br>
<br><br>
So bid 5 or 6 to go first and bring out your site, pull Sam, drop whoever else you drew, and push to 3 against anything but more than one Nazgûl. <br>
<br><br>
Move to site 4, stop.<br>
<br><br>
Then 5 and 6 in the same turn if it&#39;s not too traumatic, if your opponent chooses to lag behind (Sauron or Moria shadow players) then just match his/her pace, keeping 2 sites ahead of them. Six to 8 if you can manage a skipped archery phase (Boromir w/blade and PATHS help here).<br>
<br><br>
Eight to nine on your final turn cuz you don&#39;t want them having any more twilight or minions than necessary at site 9, do you now?<br>
<br><br>
Shadow side: I used to have a couple Worry in there to get combo-licious with Enquea, but the Uruks are exerting enough already, and Spies of Saruman is more useful. Added the Bred for Battle cuz I needed more Shadow cards and those are kinda fun, nobody usually expects those. <br>
<br><br>
Thanx for the reviews, I appreciate your thoughts. Here is my reasoning for my card choices:<br>
<br><br>
Elf allies - yeah, it&#39;s odd, but I want the variety to get the most out of Last Alliance, especially against Nazgul. I have been thinking of adding the Mirror lately. <br>
<br><br>
Secret Sentinels is going to replace Sleep, Caradhras soon.<br>
But Gift of Boats? What the heck for? Very few ppl play Valley of the Silverlode, and those that play the Ford are playing Nazgul, and there&#39;s just no possible way to get from 3 to 6 against Nazgul without killing every one of your companions off.<br>
<br><br>
Thror&#39;s Map I just don&#39;t need, except maybe for site 4. But that&#39;s not guaranteed.<br>
<br><br>
Legolas&#39;s Bow is SOOOOO worth it against Moria, and so is the Mithril Coat, cuz Frodo can face those Goblins with their Scimitars and ignore the strength from the weapons.<br>
<br><br>
Hobbit Stealth - I might switch out PATHS for another one of these.<br>
<br><br>
The Gandalfs are kinda important to me since he&#39;s usually facing Cantea when other ppl have their weapons that they can&#39;t afford to lose. <br>
<br><br>
So that&#39;s why I built it this way, but it&#39;s also why it will always be changing.<br>
<br><br>
Okay I&#39;m done w/strat for now, questions please dmail me.     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23586"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23586" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
